  "notes": [
    "This paper introduces a computational method called genetic Minimal Intervention Sets (gMIS) that extends beyond synthetic lethality to include synthetic dosage lethality and tumor suppressor gene complexes.",
    "The method integrates genome-scale metabolic networks with regulatory pathways to identify lethal genetic interventions in cancer cells.",
    "Key findings include the identification of EZH2 as essential in hematological malignancies through interactions with JUN and RELA genes."
